   <concept id="FAR_8_404" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">8.404</ph> Use of Federal Supply Schedules.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d456e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">General</i>. <xref href="Part_13.dita#FAR_Part_13"
                        base="i1112458"
                        outputclass="fm:Parts"
                        class="- topic/xref ">parts  13</xref> (except <xref href="13.303-2.dita#FAR_13_303_2"
                        base="i1111600"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">13.303-2</xref>(c)(3)), <xref href="Part_14.dita#FAR_Part_14"
                        base="i1111055"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">14</xref>, <xref href="Part_15.dita#FAR_Part_15"
                        base="i1109360"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">15</xref>, and <xref href="Part_19.dita#FAR_Part_19"
                        base="i1101928"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19</xref> (except for the requirements at <xref href="19.102.dita#FAR_19_102"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.102</xref>(b)(3) and <xref href="19.202-1.dita#FAR_19_202_1"
                        base="i1101585"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.202-1</xref>(e)(1)(iii)) do not apply to BPAs or orders placed against Federal Supply Schedules contracts (but see <xref href="8.405-5.dita#FAR_8_405_5"
                        base="i1117805"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">8.405-5</xref>). BPAs and orders placed against a MAS, using the procedures in this subpart, are considered to be issued using full and open competition (see <xref href="6.102.dita#FAR_6_102"
                        base="i1120068"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">6.102</xref>(d)(3)). Therefore, when establishing a BPA (as authorized by <xref href="13.303-2.dita#FAR_13_303_2"
                        base="i1111600"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">13.303-2</xref>(c)(3)), or placing orders under Federal Supply Schedule contracts using the procedures of <xref href="8.405.dita#FAR_8_405"
                        base="i1117528"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">8.405</xref>, ordering activities shall not seek competition outside of the Federal Supply Schedules or synopsize the requirement; but see paragraph (g) of this section.</p>
            </li>
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e52">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
               </p>
               <ol id="d456e67" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e57">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
								                 The contracting officer, when placing an order or establishing a BPA, is responsible for applying the regulatory and statutory requirements applicable to the agency for which the order is placed or the BPA is established. The requiring agency shall provide the information on the applicable regulatory and statutory requirements to the contracting officer responsible for placing the order.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e62">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> For orders over <ph rev="FAC 2025-06 October 1, 2025" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2024-001?>$750,000<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 8.404 in paragraph (b)(2) by removing “$600,000” and adding “$750,000” in its place.?></ph>, see subpart <xref href="Subpart_17.5.dita#FAR_Subpart_17_5"
                              base="i1102787"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">17.5</xref> for additional requirements for interagency acquisitions.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e70">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Acquisition planning.</i> Orders placed under a Federal Supply Schedule contract-</p>
               <ol id="d456e106" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e78">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
								                 Are not exempt from the development of acquisition plans (see <xref href="Subpart_7.1.dita#FAR_Subpart_7_1"
                              base="i1118772"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  7.1</xref>), and an information technology acquisition strategy (see <xref href="Part_39.dita#FAR_Part_39"
                              base="i1077208"
                              outputclass="fm:Part"
                              class="- topic/xref ">part  39</xref>);</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e89">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Shall comply with all FAR requirements for a consolidated or bundled contract when the order meets the definition at 
                           <xref href="2.101.dita#FAR_2_101"
                              base="i1125359"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">2.101</xref> of "consolidation" or "bundling"; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e97">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
								                 Must, whether placed by the requiring agency, or on behalf of the requiring agency, be consistent with the requiring agency’s statutory and regulatory requirements applicable to the acquisition of the supply or service.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e102">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Pricing</i>. Supplies offered on the schedule are listed at fixed prices. Services offered on the schedule are priced either at hourly rates, or at a fixed price for performance of a specific task (<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">e.g.,</i> installation, maintenance, and repair). GSA has already determined the prices of supplies and fixed-price services, and rates for services offered at hourly rates, under schedule contracts to be fair and reasonable. Therefore, ordering activities are not required to make a separate determination of fair and reasonable pricing, except for a price evaluation as required by <xref href="8.405-2.dita#FAR_8_405_2"
                        base="i1117591"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">8.405-2</xref>(d). By placing an order against a schedule contract using the procedures in <xref href="8.405.dita#FAR_8_405"
                        base="i1117528"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">8.405</xref>, the ordering activity has concluded that the order represents the best value (as defined in FAR <xref href="2.101.dita#FAR_2_101"
                        base="i1125359"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">2.101</xref>) and results in the lowest overall cost alternative (considering price, special features, administrative costs, etc.) to meet the Government’s needs. Although GSA has already negotiated fair and reasonable pricing, ordering activities may seek additional discounts before placing an order (see <xref href="8.405-4.dita#FAR_8_405_4"
                        base="i1117802"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">8.405-4</xref>).</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e125">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(e)</ph>
                  
						             The procedures under subpart <xref href="Subpart_33.1.dita#FAR_Subpart_33_1"
                        base="i1080399"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">33.1</xref> are applicable to the issuance of an order or the establishment of a BPA against a schedule contract.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e133">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(f)</ph>
                  
						             If the ordering activity issues an RFQ, the ordering activity shall provide the RFQ to any schedule contractor that requests a copy of it.</p>
            </li>
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e138">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(g)</ph>
               </p>
               <ol id="d456e204" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e143">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
								                 Ordering activities shall publicize contract actions funded in whole or in part by the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act of 2009 (Pub. L. 111-5):</p>
                     <ol id="d456e214" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e149">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              
										                     Notices of proposed MAS orders (including orders issued under BPAs) that are for "informational purposes only" exceeding $25,000 shall follow the procedures in <xref href="5.704.dita#FAR_5_704"
                                    base="i1120239"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">5.704</xref> for posting orders.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e157">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              
										                     Award notices for MAS orders (including orders issued under BPAs) shall follow the procedures in <xref href="5.705.dita#FAR_5_705"
                                    base="i1120260"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">5.705</xref>.</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e165">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
								                 When an order is awarded or a Blanket Purchase Agreement is established with an estimated value greater than the simplified acquisition threshold and supported by a limited-source justification at <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">
                           <xref href="8.405-6.dita#FAR_8_405_6"
                                 base="i1117840"
                                 outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                 class="- topic/xref ">8.405-6</xref>
                        </i>(a), the ordering activity contracting officer must-</p>
                     <ol id="d456e256" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e175">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              
										                     Publicize the action (see <xref href="5.301.dita#FAR_5_301"
                                    base="i1120562"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">5.301</xref>); and</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e183">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              
										                     Post the justification in accordance with <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">
                                 <xref href="8.405-6.dita#FAR_8_405_6"
                                       base="i1117840"
                                       outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                       class="- topic/xref ">8.405-6</xref>
                              </i>(a)(2).</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e192">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(h)</ph>
                  
						             Type-of-order preference for services.</p>
               <ol id="d456e297" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e198">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
								                 The ordering activity shall specify the order type (<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">i.e.</i>, firm-fixed price, time-and-materials, or labor-hour) for the services offered on the schedule priced at hourly rates.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e206">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
								                 Agencies shall use fixed-price orders for the acquisition of commercial services to the maximum extent practicable.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e211">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                     </p>
                     <ol id="d456e328" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e216">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              
										                     A time-and-materials or labor-hour order may be used for the acquisition of commercial services only when it is not possible at the time of placing the order to estimate accurately the extent or duration of the work or to anticipate costs with any reasonable degree of confidence.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e221">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              
										                     Prior to the issuance of a time-and-materials or labor-hour order, the contracting officer shall-</p>
                           <ol id="d456e347" class="- topic/ol ">
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e227">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(A)</ph>
                                    
												                         Execute a determination and findings (D&amp;F) for the order, in accordance with paragraph (h)(3)(iii) of this section that a fixed-price order is not suitable;</p>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e232">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(B)</ph>
                                    
												                         Include a ceiling price in the order that the contractor exceeds at its own risk; and</p>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e237">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(C)</ph>
                                    
												                         When the total performance period, including options, is more than three years, the D&amp;F prepared in accordance with this paragraph shall be signed by the contracting officer and approved by the head of the contracting activity prior to the execution of the base period.</p>
                              </li>
                           </ol>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e242">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph>
                              
										                     The D&amp;F required by paragraph (h)(3)(ii)(A) of this section shall contain sufficient facts and rationale to justify that a fixed-price order is not suitable. At a minimum, the D&amp;F shall-</p>
                           <ol id="d456e386" class="- topic/ol ">
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e248">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(A)</ph>
                                    
												                         Include a description of the market research conducted (see <xref href="#FAR_8_404"
                                          base="i1117401"
                                          outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                          class="- topic/xref ">8.404</xref>(c) and <xref href="10.002.dita#FAR_10_002"
                                          base="i1114728"
                                          outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                          class="- topic/xref ">10.002</xref>(e));</p>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e259">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(B)</ph>
                                    
												                         Establish that it is not possible at the time of placing the order to accurately estimate the extent or duration of the work or anticipate costs with any reasonable degree of confidence;</p>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e264">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(C)</ph>
                                    
												                         Establish that the current requirement has been structured to maximize the use of fixed-price orders (<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">e.g.</i>, by limiting the value or length of the time-and-materials/labor-hour order; or, establishing fixed prices for portions of the requirement) on future acquisitions for the same or similar requirements; and</p>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e272">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(D)</ph>
                                    
												                         Describe actions to maximize the use of fixed-price orders on future acquisitions for the same requirements.</p>
                              </li>
                           </ol>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e277">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iv)</ph>
                              
										                     Prior to an increase in the ceiling price of a time-and-materials or labor-hour order, the ordering activity shall-</p>
                           <ol id="d456e443" class="- topic/ol ">
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e283">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(A)</ph>
                                    
												                         Conduct an analysis of pricing and other relevant factors to determine if the action is in the best interest of the Government and document the order file;</p>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e288">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(B)</ph>
                                    
												                         Follow the procedures at <xref href="8.405-6.dita#FAR_8_405_6"
                                          base="i1117840"
                                          outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                          class="- topic/xref ">8.405-6</xref> for a change that modifies the general scope of the order; and</p>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e296">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(C)</ph>
                                    
												                         Comply with the requirements at <xref href="8.402.dita#FAR_8_402"
                                          base="i1117315"
                                          outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                          class="- topic/xref ">8.402</xref>(f) when modifying an order to add open market items.</p>
                              </li>
                           </ol>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e304">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                  
						             Ensure that service contractor reporting requirements are met in accordance with <xref href="Subpart_4.17.dita#FAR_Subpart_4_17"
                        base="i1121341"
                        outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                        class="- topic/xref ">subpart  4.17</xref>, Service Contracts Inventory.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d470e312">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(j)</ph>
                  
						             Line items. When placing orders or establishing BPAs, ordering activities shall reference the special item number and the corresponding line or subline item awarded (established per <xref href="4.1005.dita#FAR_4_1005"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">4.1005</xref>) in the schedule. If an ordering activity contracting officer adds an item not on the Federal Supply Schedule in accordance with <xref href="8.402.dita#FAR_8_402"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">8.402</xref>(f), establish a new line item in accordance with <xref href="Subpart_4.10.dita#FAR_Subpart_4_10"
                        outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                        class="- topic/xref ">subpart  4.10</xref>.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
